Interface InterfaceArbitraryEnzymeKinetics

All Superinterfaces:
InterfaceKinteticsType
All Known Implementing Classes:
CommonModularRateLaw, ConvenienceKinetics, DirectBindingModularRateLaw, ForceDependentModularRateLaw, IrrevNonModulatedNonInteractingEnzymes, PowerLawModularRateLaw, SimultaneousBindingModularRateLaw
public interface InterfaceArbitraryEnzymeKinetics
extends InterfaceKinteticsType

Kinetic law objects that implement this interface are able to describe any enzyme-catalyzed process whether or not an enzyme is explicitely assigned to the reaction. In this context, arbitrary means that the stoichiometry of reactants and products can be any real or integer number.
